SIMPLE: forbid
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forbid
<hw>For*bid"</hw> <pr>(f⟦ocr⟧r*b⟦icr⟧d")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Forbade</conjf>
<pr>(f⟦ocr⟧r*b⟦acr⟧d")</pr>; <pos>p. p.</pos> <conjf>Forbidden</conjf>
<pr>(f⟦ocr⟧r*b⟦icr⟧d"d'n)</pr> (<conjf>Forbid</conjf>,
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>); <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Forbidding</conjf> <pr>(f⟦ocr⟧r*b⟦icr⟧d"d⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[OE. <ets>forbeden</ets>, AS. <ets>forbe⟦oacute⟧dan</ets>; pref.
<ets>for-</ets> + <ets>be⟦oacute⟧dan</ets> to bid; akin to D.
<ets>verbieden</ets>, G. <ets>verbieten</ets>, Icel.
<ets>fyrirbj⟦omac⟧⟦edh⟧a</ets>, <ets>forbo⟦edh⟧a</ets>, Sw.
<ets>f⟦oum⟧rbjuda</ets>, Dan. <ets>forbyde</ets>. See <er>Bid</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To command against, or contrary
to; to prohibit; to interdict.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>More than I have said . . . ⟦br⟧
The leisure and enforcement of the time⟦br⟧
<qex>Forbids</qex> to dwell upon.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To deny, exclude from, or warn off, by express
command; to command not to enter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Have I not <qex>forbid</qex> her my house?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To oppose, hinder, or prevent, as if by an effectual
command; <as>as, an impassable river <ex>forbids</ex> the approach of
the army</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A blaze of glory that <qex>forbids</qex> the sight.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To accurse; to blast.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He shall live a man <qex>forbid</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To defy; to challenge.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>L. Andrews.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To prohibit; interdict; hinder; preclude;
withhold; restrain; prevent. See <er>Prohibit</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forbid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Forbid
<hw>For*bid"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To utter a
prohibition; to prevent; to hinder.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧I did not or
<xex>forbid</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forbiddance</ent>⟦br⟧
